Package ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.stack

Class Stack<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.stack.Stack<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    public class Stack<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    An automatically-resizable implementation of a stack data structure. Supports all basic stack methods, and permits all objects. peek() and pop() returns Optional, so null-values are treated as Optional.empty().
    See Also:
    Optional, Cloneable

      • popStack

        public Stack<T> popStack​(int elemAmount)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Extracts elemAmount top elements from a stack and returns a stack consisting of them.

        If the size of the stack is less than elemAmount, the method is applied to the whole stack.

        Parameters:
        elemAmount - an amount of elements to extract
        Returns:
        a stack composed of extracted elements
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if elemAmount is negative

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object obj)
        Compares the specified object with this stack for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a stack, both stacks have the same size, and all corresponding pairs of elements in the two lists are equal. In other words, two stacks are defined to be equal if they contain the same elements in the same order.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
